node.text:
It’s Earth Day today. Many may encounter a cute Google doodle or reminders on their FYPs. But at Koenigsegg, being environmentally conscious is a lifelong commitment. 

We are propulsion-agnostic – equally in on bleeding edge electrification as we are in on renewable liquid fuels that can be combusted clean and Co2-neutral. We seek the best solution for each challenge – always with the environment at the forefront, without compromising on ultimate performance. This can end up in a full EV, clean combustion or a mix thereof.

The world’s first environmentally conscious production sportscar, the 2007 "Flower Power" Koenigsegg CCXR, was designed according to this exact philosophy, to run on E85 and E100 biofuels. In the same vein, our sister company Freevalve develops variable valve systems capable of running fully renewable fuels in any climate – a system adopted in the Gemera’s Tiny Friendly Giant engine.

Our holistic view will continue to manifest itself in our bright and green future ahead so stay tuned for even more exciting developments!

node.text:
Koenigsegg currently occupies the hangars that previously belonged to the Swedish Airforce F10 Squadron. 

They were also known as the Ghost Squadron because they would take off in the early morning mist and only land after dark – people never saw them but they heard them alright. In honor of them, we have since marked all our cars with their ghost emblem as well as named our community of customers, fans and staff the Ghost Squadron. 

We cannot help but be reminded of this at a poignant moment captured last week as the cars drove towards Pebble Beach amid a heavy mist.

📷: @oskarbakke

Our dear Ghost Squadron family in the US. While our showcars has been touring over the Americas, it’s been some time since many of us have been physically around to meet and speak with you – our beloved customers, fans and dealers.
 
We are super excited to be participating in Monterey Car Week (13-15 Aug) where the Gemera, the Jesko Absolut, and a special Regera will be on show, alongside the first time a special CCR will be making an appearance on US soil. Some of our amazing customers will also be turning up with their amazing Koenigseggs and we are eager to be making a big impression this year.
 
We can’t wait to see everyone again! 

-
 
The health and safety of everyone is our priority. We ask that we be close at heart but remember to keep safe distance.

Let's get upfront and real for a bit. At Koenigsegg, while we pursue perfection centered on ultimate performance, we're also a grounded bunch.

We see the trail of destruction in the wake of the devasting floods in Western Germany and cannot stand idly by. We have decided to use our pre-series production Jesko for some good. It's not ideal for ferrying people but in all seriousness, we hope its image help raise some funds for volunteer groups and the district of Ahrweiler, Germany that took a big hit. 

From now until 9th Aug, we will release a special small series of A2-size prints of the Jesko. All proceeds will go to recovery efforts. Links in stories on where you can purchase these limited posters. More information in product descriptions on other platforms you can contribute to.

[Done in collaboration with DasProduktionsbüro and @kenozache]
